import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import time
import seaborn as sns

Funkcje do pomiaru skuteczności¶

plot_confusion_matrix -> macierz pomyłek

calculate_metrics -> Czułość (sensitivity) i swoistość (specificity).

plot_roc_curve -> wykres krzywej roc

In [166]:
def plot_confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred, labels=None):
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)
    disp = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confusion_matrix=cm, display_labels=labels)
    disp.plot(cmap="Blues", values_format="d")
    plt.title("Macierz Pomyłek")
    plt.show()


def calculate_metrics(y_true, y_pred):
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred).ravel()
    sensitivity = tp / (tp + fn) if (tp + fn) > 0 else 0
    specificity = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) > 0 else 0
    return sensitivity, specificity

def plot_roc_curve(y_true, y_scores):
    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_true, y_scores)
    roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, color='blue', label=f'ROC Curve (AUC = {roc_auc:.2f})')
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='red', linestyle='--', label='Losowa klasyfikacja')
    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate (1 - Specificity)')
    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate (Sensitivity)')
    plt.title('Krzywa ROC')
    plt.legend(loc='lower right')
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

Implementacja analitycznej wersji klasyfikacji liniowej¶

Klasyfikacji liniowa z regularyzacją Tichonowa

In [170]:
def train_tichonow(X_train, y_train, X_test, lambda_reg):
    y_train = np.where(y_train == 0, -1, 1)
    
    I = np.eye(X_train.shape[1])  
    I[0, 0] = 0 
    w = np.linalg.inv(X_train.T @ X_train + lambda_reg * I) @ X_train.T @ y_train
    
    y_pred = (X_test @ w > 0).astype(int)
    return y_pred, w

Implementacja przy użyciu Sklearn¶

sklearn.linear_model.RidgeClassifier

In [171]:
from sklearn.linear_model import RidgeClassifier

def ridge_classifier(X_train, y_train, X_test, alpha=1.0):
    model = RidgeClassifier(alpha=alpha)
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    
    return y_pred

    _, w = train_tichonow(X_train_copy, y_train_copy, X_test_copy, 0.01)
end_time = time.time()

h = 0.01
x_min, x_max = X_train_copy[:, 1].min() - 0.2, X_train_copy[:, 1].max() + 1
y_min, y_max = X_train_copy[:, 2].min() - 0.2, X_train_copy[:, 2].max() + 1
xx, yy = np.meshgrid(np.arange(x_min, x_max, h),
                        np.arange(y_min, y_max, h))
grid_points = np.c_[xx.ravel(), yy.ravel()]
grid_points = np.hstack((np.ones((grid_points.shape[0], 1)), grid_points))
Z, w = train_tichonow(X_train_copy, y_train_copy, grid_points, 0.01)
Z = Z.reshape(xx.shape)

plt.contourf(xx, yy, Z, alpha=0.3, cmap=plt.cm.coolwarm)

plt.ylabel("Feature 2")

bias, w1, w2= w
y_vals = -(bias + w1 * x_vals) / w2

y_min, y_max = X_train_copy[:, 1].min() - 0.2, X_train_copy[:, 1].max() + 0.2

In [183]:
stats = []
for column in X.columns:
    mean = data[column].mean()
    mode = data[column].mode()[0]
    std_dev = data[column].std()
    min_val = data[column].min()
    max_val = data[column].max()
    unique_values = data[column].nunique()
    total_values = len(data[column])
    feature_type = "Kategoryczna" if unique_values / total_values < 0.05 else "Ciągła"
    
    stats.append({
        "Cecha": column,
        "Średnia": mean,
        "Dominanta": mode,
        "Odchylenie standardowe": std_dev,
        "Minimum": min_val,
        "Maksimum": max_val,
        "Typ cechy": feature_type
    })

print(pd.DataFrame(stats))

Automatyczny wybór 4 cech¶

W oparciu o RidgeClassifier z sklearn i sklearn.feature_selection.SequentialFeatureSelector wybrane 4 najlepsze cechy

In [190]:
from sklearn.feature_selection import SequentialFeatureSelector
from sklearn.linear_model import RidgeClassifier

ridge_model = RidgeClassifier(alpha=1.0)
sfs = SequentialFeatureSelector(ridge_model, n_features_to_select=4, direction='forward')
sfs.fit(X, y)
